Following an ANC National Executive Committee meeting that went late into Monday night, the party announced that it will be holding a media briefing at Luthuli House to communicate the outcomes. Watch live.After surviving an unparalleled attack on his leadership of the ANC, a defiant President Jacob Zuma has told the party's national executive committee that stepping down would be like handing himself over to the enemy and he would never do it.The &ldquo;surprise&rdquo; motion by Tourism Minister Derek Hanekom for Zuma to step down or be recalled was defeated.&nbsp;Hanekom, Thulas Nxesi and Aaron Motsoaledi called for his head, supported by senior NEC members. It was reported that Science and Technology Minister Naledi Pandor also supported the anti-Zuma motion.Standing behind him were Malusi &shy;Gigaba (Home Affairs), Fikile Mbalula (Sport and Reaction) and his former wife, Dr &shy;Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, chair of the African Union, &shy;eNCA reported.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.